This paper deals with image segmentation and classification for medical diagnosis, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also introduces a novel network architecture, which could potentially be of interest to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) community. Additionally, the use of medical images suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
